HEADWORD: Tergite
<hw>Ter"gite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The dorsal portion of an arthromere or somite of an articulate
animal. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Coleoptera</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

